Russian Equity Movers: Norilsk Nickel, Rosneft, VTB Group

-- B y   J a s o n   C o r c o r a n
-- 
2011-09-01T15:27:17Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-01/russian-equity-movers-norilsk-nickel-rosneft-vtb-group.html
The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  rose for a
fifth day, increasing 0.4 percent to 1,551.58 by the 6:45 p.m.
close in Moscow. The dollar-denominated RTS Index advanced 0.1
percent to 1,703.86 rubles.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.  OAO GMK Norilsk Nickel (GMKN RX), Russia’s biggest mining
company, slid as nickel and copper both fell in  London . Its
shares slipped as much as 3.4 percent before closing 0.2 percent
lower at 7,199 rubles.  OAO Rosneft (ROSN RX), the country’s largest oil producer,
increased for a fifth day as crude traded near a one-month high
in  New York . The shares added 1.6 percent to 231.30 rubles, the
highest closing level since Aug. 2.  VTB Group (VTBR RX) climbed after  Russia ’s second-biggest
bank more than doubled second-quarter profit to a record as it
boosted lending and recorded fewer bad loans. The stock erased
earlier losses of as much as 3 percent to close 1 percent higher
at 7.58 kopeks.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jason Corcoran at 
